Nov. 2⁴· But if you think, My son, what fruit these toils will bring, A quick end and a very great reward, You will have no trouble from them, But a great comfort for your patience. For for this little bit of will you have now freely given, ’ You shall for ever have your will in heaven. There shall you find all you wish, All you can desire, There at your hand shall be abundance of all good, No fear of loss.
